OL,3,C'They were less than human': Britain's
OL,4,Cforced adoption scandal
OL,6,FFiona Cahill's mother, Maria, was born
OL,7,Fin a Red Cross mother and baby home in
OL,8,FLondon in 1954, but as a newborn baby
OL,9,Fwas sent to one of Ireland's most
OL,10,Fnotorious institutions with her mother
OL,11,FPhilomena, who was unmarried.
OL,13,FPhilomena had moved from Ireland to
OL,14,FLondon for work as a teenager and
OL,15,Flater met Maria's father. Like
OL,16,Fthousands of others, she was labelled
OL,17,Fas a 'PFI'.
