OL,3,C'They were less than human': Britain's
OL,4,Cforced adoption scandal
OL,6,FIn the 1950s and 60s, a pregnant,
OL,7,Funmarried women from Ireland was
OL,8,Freduced to an acronym by social
OL,9,Fworkers in England - PFI which stood
OL,10,Ffor 'pregnant from Ireland'.
OL,12,FAt that time, thousands of young women
OL,13,Fhad fled Ireland to avoid the brutal
OL,14,Finstitutions there, but they found
OL,15,FBritain to be an unwelcoming place and
OL,16,Fdifferent forces conspired to pressure
OL,17,Fwomen to give up their babies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
