OL,3,C'They were less than human': Britain's
OL,4,Cforced adoption scandal
OL,6,FThe British authorities saw them as a
OL,7,Fburden on the public purse, while the
OL,8,FCatholic Church in Ireland wanted to
OL,9,Fkeep babies in their faith.
OL,11,FThe result was an organised
OL,12,Frepatriation scheme where journeys
OL,13,Fwere organised and paid for by the
OL,14,Fstate and the church.
OL,16,FFiona, 50, who is an artist and carer,
OL,17,Fcontacted ITV News after seeing our
OL,18,Fongoing investigation in historic
OL,19,Fforced adoption.
