OL,3,C'They were less than human': Britain's
OL,4,Cforced adoption scandal
OL,6,FSurvivors are now campaigning for
OL,7,Fcompensation from both Irish and
OL,8,FBritish governments ` who they say
OL,9,Fwere directly involved in the 'brutal'
OL,10,Frepatriation scheme from 1930 to the
OL,11,Flate 1970s.
OL,13,FIn March, Labour MP Liam Conlon, who
OL,14,Fis the national chair of the Labour
OL,15,FParty Irish Society, introduced
OL,16,FPhilomena's Law to support the 13,000
OL,17,Fsurvivors of Ireland's mother and baby
OL,18,Fhomes in Britain.
